GEITA Gold head coach Hassan Banyai has warned Boma FC to expect turbulence when they meet on Sunday at Nyankumbu Girls Secondary School ground here. Speaking about his team’s preparation ahead of the clash, Banyai said his players are well drilled and he is confident that they will work hard to ensure they win their home match. The former Majimaji FC, Moro United and Njombe Mji FC coach said they now have nine remaining matches, five of them at home and four others away. Geita Gold home matches will be against Boma FC this Sunday, then Rhino Rangers, Mgambo Shooting and Transit Camp. Away matches will be against Pamba FC at Nyamagana Stadium in Mwanza, Mashujaa FC at Lake Tanganyika Stadium in Kigoma, Dodoma FC at Jamhuri Stadium in Dodoma and Mgambo Shooting at Ally Hassan Mwinyi Stadium in Tabora. Banyai also confirmed the return of the midfielder Jonathan Mwaibibi, who missed their last weekend match against Police Tanzania at Ushirika Stadium in Kilimanjaro. He called upon the team’s fans and supporters in Geita Region to continue supporting their team wholeheartedly in all their remaining games. Geita Gold are now leading the pack with 26 points after 13 outings. They have won seven, lost one and drawn five matches. They have netted fourteen and conceded seven goals.